The paper deals with a streaming algorithm for estimating the $\ell_2$ norm of a frequency vector, which is a problem in data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The algorithm uses the \textsf{CountSketch} data structure, which is a popular tool in sketching and compressive sensing, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SY). Finally, the algorithm achieves a constant update time, which is a result in computational complexity (cs.CC).
